        What is an open science digital space?
      </div>
      <div class="collapse-content !px-0"> 
        <div class="prose">
          <p>A “digital space” is a product or place online where multiple people can interact with one another. Some digital spaces are home to only one community, while others are products that host multiple communities. The organization building the digital space controls the user experience and the governance of that space. </p>
          <p>An Open Science digital space includes a set of features and UX specific to foster open science practices This means the space is intentionally developed to support the sharing of knowledge, collaboration, and transparency in scientific research and discovery, as outlined in the features section.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
